content:
When you define an augment transformation, you set the action attribute to augment and specify the parameters.

The following table describes the input parameters.

PARAMETER	REQUIRED?	VALUE
operation	No	

Indicates what the transformation does if it matches multiple rows in the right dataset with a row in the left. Valid values:
LookupSingleValue. Returns values from one of the matched rows.
LookupMultiValue. Returns values from all matched rows.

left	Yes	Node in the dataflow definition file that identifies the left dataset.
left_key	Yes	

Key column in the left dataset used to augment the dataset. If you use a composite key, the left and right keys must have the same number of columns in the same order.

right	Yes	Node in the dataflow definition file that identifies the right dataset.
relationship	Yes	Relationship between the left and right dataset.
right_select	Yes	An array of column names from the right dataset to include in the output dataset.
right_key	Yes	

Key column in the right dataset used to augment the dataset. If you use a composite key, the left and right keys must have the same number of columns in the same order.

For more information about each operation, see Special Cases for Matching Records with the augment Transformation.
title: Configuring the Augment Transformation in CRM Analytics
